- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant because the paper deals with context-free grammars, which are a fundamental concept in formal language theory.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant because the simplification of grammars is important in natural language processing, which is a subfield of computational linguistics.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant because the simplification of grammars can be seen as a problem in algorithm design and optimization.
